    displayTitle: "Cornflower",
    lines: ["The floor is never quite as clean as I want it to be and it bothers me more than I say. There are so many things I will never say and there are so many things I will never hear. I will stand at my mothers grave with a mouth full of things I wish I could have said. My posters are melting off the wall and the clouds are breaking into my room and we don't really talk anymore but I still have to be brave. Every day I have to be brave. Every day I stand up and I look in the mirror and I smile to the sky and I put on my face and I clean the grime and I write my poems and every day my head thrums with the angsty restlessness of an overstayed visit. Every day I numb and numb the pain until it cycles around again and the pain is all I feel. Grief is a spiral staircase and time is moving on without me. Time is moving on but I am still smelling your perfume in the elevator and seeing your smile in the flowers and time is moving on but I am still sitting at your doorstep with a postcard and a color that made me think of you."]
