    title: null,
    displayTitle: "10.8.24",
    lines: ["The light in my window casts shadows I don’t recognize, but they still feel like home. Every day I sit on the edge of something. My bed, the subway platform, a memory. ","","I pretend a lot. I pretend the clock on the wall isn’t racing ahead, that the moon doesn’t know the secrets I’ve spilled to it in the dead of night. I pretend that grief is something I can outrun if I just keep moving, but no matter how far I go, I end up back in the playground near your house, carrying flowers you’ll never see, whispering words you’ll never hear.","","There’s something about the way the universe keeps spinning that feels like a betrayal. Stars flicker out every day, and we keep living. Planets collide, and we still go to work, tie our shoes, and clean the grease out of our hair, even though we know it will return tomorrow. I tell myself that this is just the way of things, that the sun will rise whether or not I’m here to watch it. But in the moments between, when the sky is neither dark nor light, I wonder if the universe ever pauses for me, just for a second, just to see if I’ll catch up.","","But I don’t. I stare at the moon, I hold its gaze like an old lover’s, and I wonder if it feels as lost as I do.","","We’re all just pretending, aren’t we? Just waiting for the day when we can finally say we’ve arrived, when the dust settles, and we’re no longer haunted by the things we didn’t say.","","Until then, I keep pretending. I wake up, I clean the dirt off my shoes, and I step outside. I look at the stars and think, maybe tonight they’ll speak."]
