    id: "poem-20",
    date: "11.5.24",
    title: "11:11",
    displayTitle: "11:11",
    lines: ["October is finally over and the weather is starting to cool down again. The nip of the wind burns ever so gently at first, though I know it soon will bite my skin with the intensity to match my draining mental state. I am still hiding in so many ways because the more I try to leave my closet the more I fear I will step in lava. I trust too easily, but not easily enough. I want to be happy. I just want to be happy. But I can’t yet. Something is in my way, and the mirror bumps into me again and again. The mirror won’t let me be happy. Not yet, she says. Not until I’ve suffered. But October is over. Did I not suffer enough in October? On the edge of a ledge, on the edge of my bed, on the edge of consciousness, did I not suffer enough in October? I have learned enough lessons. I’m ready to come back. I want to feel pain, I want to cry, I want to hurt, and I want to start making progress again. I want moderation and I want control. ","","Maybe all the wanting is getting in the way of it happening. Maybe all this overthinking blocks out my chance to actually process and change my behavior. Maybe I am getting better, but I just can’t appreciate it yet. Maybe I’m so much closer than I realize. ","","Maybe it’s just really hard to be 19."]
