    title: null,
    displayTitle: "12.12.24",
    lines: ["I am out of money and I am out of time. I walk and it rains so I stay inside until it stops raining. I am a vessel for all emotions, I am a bullet and a vest. I carve out my heart from a chunk of rock and I carve out a rock from pieces of my heart. I go out to walk and the rain starts up so I sit in the rain. I am out of rhythm and I am out of rhyme. I can’t run anymore but the open road calls for me to drive. The car was white. Or was it black? Things are so hazy sometimes and there is still so much I have to figure out. The rain hasn't stopped but the sun is out and the question is stronger than me but I am stronger than the answer. I want so badly to live but all I can do is write and when I start living all I want is to fill the page. I fear forgetting, I fear forgiveness, I fear love. I scrubbed myself raw in the shower only to realize I let myself drip down the drain. I am the dirt and grime just as I am the shiny pearly interior. My laundry isn't done and my room is a mess and my dad will be here soon. Will I die of old age? Will my parents? Will the earth? I am still bullet and I am shield. I am question and answer. I finished carving my heart but I am not yet ready. I run through the rain against the wind and my clothes dry on the hangers in my messy room where I lay in bed and rot through the floor. "]
