    lines: ["My vision is blurry and my eyes are crusted over with the wretched droppings of sleep. My vision is blurry and my eyes are as heavy as my soul and a feather falls from a falcon flying in the cold night sky. The lights shine like infected diamonds, growing in my vision as I blink and the crust falls from my eyes. I am radiant and I am cold. I am shining star and I am moldy bread in my fridge that grows due to my negligence. I smell warm tea and I touch the clouds and I taste the light and I hear the music. And the ringing. My vision is blurry and my eyes are crusted over but I haven't been awake in months and I haven't heard a voice in years. The falcon flies away into the vast night sky and the moon smiles down at me from another time. I am the crust in my eyes just as I am the falcon and the moon and the knife and the tea. I am everything that fades to green and everything that grows mold when untouched. As a mirror does. As a statue does. As do we all. "]
